===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To insert (a graft) in a [[branch]] or [[stem]] of another tree; to [[propagate]] by [[insertion]] in another [[stock]]; also, to insert a graft upon.
# {{context|transitive|surgery|lang=en}} To [[implant]] a portion of (living flesh or akin) in a [[lesion]] so as to form an organic union.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To join (one thing) to another as if by grafting, so as to bring about a close union.
#: 1717 ''Eloisa to Abelard. '' And '''graft''' my love immortal on thy fame! — [[w:Alexander Pope|Alexander Pope]]
# {{context|transitive|nautical|lang=en}} To cover, as a ring [[bolt]], [[block]] [[strap]], [[splicing]], etc., with a [[weaving]] of small [[cord]] or [[rope-yarns]].
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To insert [[scion|scions]] (grafts) from one tree, or kind of tree, etc., into another; to practice grafting.

